---
description: Defines the preferred order of class members in TypeScript/JavaScript classes
globs: ["**/*.ts", "**/*.tsx"]
alwaysApply: true
---

Class member ordering (top to bottom):
1. Static properties (public, protected, private)
2. Instance properties (public, protected, private)
3. Constructor
4. Static methods (public, protected, private)
5. Instance methods (public, protected, private)

Within each category, order by:
- Public members first
- Protected members second
- Private members last

Example:
```typescript
class Example {
  // 1. Static properties
  public static readonly PUBLIC_STATIC = 'public';
  protected static PROTECTED_STATIC = 'protected';
  private static PRIVATE_STATIC = 'private';

  // 2. Instance properties
  public readonly publicProp: string;
  protected protectedProp: string;
  private privateProp: string;

  // 3. Constructor
  constructor() {
    // initialization
  }

  // 4. Static methods
  public static publicStaticMethod() {}
  protected static protectedStaticMethod() {}
  private static privateStaticMethod() {}

  // 5. Instance methods
  public publicMethod() {}
  protected protectedMethod() {}
  private privateMethod() {}
}
```
